---
/**
 * Testimonials — editorial voices from every stakeholder who matters.
 *
 * Cancer lens: "Who got seen and who got left out?"
 * Pisces lens: dignity — these are people, not outcomes. Human labels,
 *   no before/after reduction, a quiet line acknowledging consent.
 * Leo lens: recognition lives in its own section below (Recognition.astro),
 *   so warmth and credibility don't compete here.
 *
 * Design intent: no boxes. Each voice sits in open space so the reader
 * focuses on the words. Photo entries alternate sides; text-only entries
 * anchor left behind a hairline accent.
 *
 * This section ships with 8 voices as a menu, not a target. Most pages
 * read best with 4–5 — enough for range (a participant, a partner, a
 * donor, a staff or board voice) without out-weighing the sections around
 * it. Libra: a testimonial wall that runs longer than the problem and
 * recognition sections combined tips the page off balance. Delete down to
 * the voices that actually apply.
 */

// Video is a local MP4 served from /public/video, played with native
// controls below — no third-party embed, no external script.
---

<section class="section testimonials-section" aria-labelledby="testimonials-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow">Voices</span>
    <h2 id="testimonials-heading" class="sr-only">The care behind the program</h2>

    <!-- LEAD QUOTE — the line that earns the scroll. Stands alone. -->
    <blockquote class="testimonials-lead reveal-feature">
      <span class="testimonials-lead-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
      <p>A major part of my success was the treatments and therapy I received from Dr. Vas.</p>
      <footer class="testimonials-lead-footer">
        <cite>Adam Folker</cite>
        <span class="testimonials-lead-context">Collegiate &amp; professional basketball player</span>
      </footer>
    </blockquote>

    <!-- VIDEO TESTIMONIAL — local MP4, native controls, click to play.
         Luke Hudson is a patient of Dr. Vas (not a veteran): this is
         "the care is real" proof, not a program-participant story. -->
    <figure class="testimonial-video reveal-feature">
      <div class="testimonial-video-frame">
        <video
          class="testimonial-video-player"
          controls
          preload="metadata"
          playsinline
        >
          <source src="/video/luke-hudson-testimonial.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          Your browser doesn&rsquo;t support embedded video.
        </video>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="testimonial-video-caption">
        <span class="section-kicker">A patient&rsquo;s story</span>
        Luke Hudson on the care he received from Dr. Vas — the same clinical
        standard behind every Better in 90 plan.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="testimonial-flow">

      <!-- Adam Folker — real, fully attributed. The fuller story. -->
      <article class="testimonial-entry text-only">
        <div class="testimonial-quote">
          <span class="section-kicker">In his words</span>
          <blockquote>
            During my sophomore year in college, I had hip surgery that was
            potentially season-ending and even career-ending. My coaches referred
            me to Dr. Vas, who was able to take care of me and eventually get me
            back to playing within a short few weeks. That season I ended up
            winning hustle player of the year. Throughout my career I saw Dr. Vas
            for injuries and preventive care, and I was able to play competitively
            at the top level.
          </blockquote>
          <cite>Adam Folker &middot; Collegiate &amp; professional basketball player</cite>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>

    <!-- Honest care line — every quote here is real and fully attributed. -->
    <p class="testimonials-note">
      Shared with permission.
    </p>

    <!-- ── SECTION BRIDGE ── Libra: carries people → recognition so the
         group reads as one arc (problem → people → proof). Shared motif,
         styled in sections.css. ── -->
    <div class="section-bridge" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="section-bridge-line"></span>
      <span class="section-bridge-chevron">&darr;</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
